About About

A business development executive leading activities in relationship management and strategic planning, focusing on opportunities at Health and Human Services (HHS), with particular focus at the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services (CMS).

After working at CMS for eight years, I have accrued an additional 15 years of experience at multiple companies winning tens of millions of dollars in contract awards across federal and state healthcare markets. With my knowledge and connections, I assist small and medium-sized companies to identify, research and qualify opportunities; make introductions to my former colleagues; and help identify and secure positions on proposal teams with the highest probability of success.

Possessing a law degree and a masters degree in health administration, I also have over thirty years of health policy and analytics experience in the healthcare industry. My expertise lies predominately in the areas of quality improvement/performance measurement, compliance, and new financing and delivery models.
